This paper is about neural machine translation (NMT), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper discusses the calibration of NMT models, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) and optimization (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions attention-based models, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.NE.
